Cell["\<\
In mathematics, Weingarten functions are rational functions indexed by \
partitions of integers that can be used to calculate integrals of products of \
matrix coefficients over classical groups. They were first studied by \
Weingarten (1978) who found their asymptotic behavior, and named by Collins \
(2003), who evaluated them explicitly for the unitary group.\
\>", "Notes",
 CellID->1475656596,ExpressionUUID->"7226bce9-80cf-479c-840d-dd260ed91a0a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The implementation is based on the Murnaghan-Nakayama algorithm (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["Bernstein, 2004"]], 
    "https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jsc.2003.11.001"},
   "WebLink",
   BaseStyle->{"Notes"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "67d3923c-5e7f-420b-9e2a-998b0650a1aa"],
 ") to compute the characters of the symmetric group."
}], "Notes",
 CellID->565881315,ExpressionUUID->"a40427de-b4d2-4af8-a522-0b2fc6f8e092"]
}, Dynamic[CurrentValue[
 EvaluationNotebook[], {TaggingRules, "Openers", "NotesSection"}, Closed]]]],

